Serves 4
There are 2 parts to this: soup and (optional) fritters
/////
Fritters:
  Grate:
      1-2 zucchini
      1 small beetroot
  Add a tablespoon or so of salt and leave a while for the water to drain from the zucchini (i.e. while the soup cooks)
  Once it's drained, squeeze the water out and then mix in:
      Half a red onion finely diced
      A handful of herbs (coriander / dill / parsley)
      Salt and pepper
      Chickpea flour, one tablespoon at a time till it's a paste that just holds together (add a touch of water if it's too dry)
  When the soup is ready, fry little fritters.
/////
Soup:
  In a pot fry on low heat:
      1 finely diced brown onion
      Finely diced / minced ginger (about 1 tablespoon)
      1 finely diced chilli (or teaspoon chilli flakes)
  When the onion is nice and soft, add:
      1 tablespoon ground cumin
      1 teaspoon smoked paprika
      1 tablespoon of tomato paste
  Fry just 1 minute.
  Add:
      1 cup / 200g dried red lentils (stir to coat for a few seconds)
      2 cups chicken stock
      Optional: Roughly chopped button mushrooms
  Simmer for 15 minutes or until lentils are cooked
  Add:
      Chopped rocket
  Simmer a few minutes longer
  Add:
      Juice of half a lemon
/////
Serve soup with fritters and yoghurt
